[00:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The question we asked ourselves is what would creative work actually look like in the age of unified intelligence. When you have this amount of power, how do you work with it? But AI for such work today looks like a'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mess. The best solution right now that people have come up with is the spaghetti of nodes, which we call node monsters at Luma. Issue is we hear from our customers that they spend more'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'time building the tooling than actually using it. And you know why? Because there\'s really nothing intelligent here. [music] It\'s plumbing. Introducing Luma Agents.'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI collaborators with unified intelligence. These can perform end-to-end creative work and be a part of your team. Luma Agents produce work that understand'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; the world. Accurate lighting, real physics, coherent spaces, believable materials. It\'s the only one you will ever need. Next, Luma Agents [music] see everything. Your entire project across'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'every modality, every image, every [music] video, every document, revision, script that you\'ve ever made. All of it and all at once. It\'s not sufficient to just do the work.'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Luma Agents can actually look at what they made and judge it. Does it match the lighting in the reference? Does the Is the composition balanced? Does this feel on brand? Is it physically accurate? This is what made'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'coding agents as powerful as they are. It\'s not generation of code, it\'s evaluation and running the code. Next is multiplayer collaboration. Luma Agents are built from the ground up for multiplayer.'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Your team and AI Agents working on the same board at the same time. Your team can split up. One person art directing hero shots, another refining copy, another building a video. All on the same board, all with Agents, all'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sharing the same context. So, all of these capabilities come together into what we call task completion. You give Luma agent a brief, it plans the'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'work, breaks it into steps, generating across formats evaluation evaluating its work along the way, and comes back to you when it needs your eye. You you guide the things, it builds it. Not one image, but a campaign. Not a draft, but'

